Text.Value: |Vlaakith.. You couldn't be farther from the truth.|
|Serve Vlaaktih|
|I want to help you, but I cannot give away this artefact easily.|
[DID CRECHE]  |I visited the Creche nearby. You're following Vlaakith's orders too.|
|Why is everyone so desperate for this artefact?|
|Don't be swayed by this traitor. Thanks to Gith himself, our people are the world's conquerors.|
|You are making a grave mistake. Vlaakith will bring our people to ruin!|
[DID ASTRAL PRISON] |Orpheus? It's Daisy the one in there, you're mistaken.|
|Don't listen to her! Orpheus is the only way forward!|
|I think we didn't start off with the right foot. Let me introduce myself.|
|Serving Vlaakith is an honor and duty.|
|You will die now. *Casts a spell on the dragon*. Kill them, Dragon!|
|Not a step further. Hand over the artefact.|
|A githyanki revolution? That has nothing to do with me, please leave.|
|Very good. Follow your orders and kill the traitor. I will enjoy the spectacle.|
|*Serving your Queen... or helping free Orpheus.*|
|Things are more complicated than they- |
|I need the artefact that you carry. The whole fate of the our race depends on it.|
|What was that? What are you not telling me?|
|*You can't help but think this decision might shape up the future of your people.*|
|Lae'zel. Kill the traitor. Your Queen is watching you closely.|
|We escaped slavery before, but we still think like slaves.|
|Vlaakith is willing to give you another chance.|
[ALREADY MET VOSS] |We already met once, Kithrak Voss. We've been over this already.|
|I recall your name, Lae'zel. An outstanding pupil, pride of the cr√®che K'liir. You're a true follower of Gith.|
|Your time has ended, Voss. You've been under our watch for long, and your treachery ends now.|
|Help Oprheus|
|Who is Orpheus, what the hell are you going on about?|
|Vlaakith's inquisitors have been keeping track of you.|
|I am the one who fought with our Prince, and the one who failed and doomed us to tyranny.|
|*Suddenly a portal opens and a few Githyanki exit out of it and move to surround the party.*|
|I apologize for causing damage to your camp. I made sure no one is harmed.|
|What you have is the solution that will free us. It imprisons the Prince in the shooting star: Orpheus. We are a revolution.|
|You're the one who killed W'Wargaz. Such treachery also hides strength.|
|Dragon, kill them!|
|Traitors everywhere. One after another.|
|*You suddenly feel weak and your head stings with sharp pain... As the moment passes, you start feeling normal again.*|
|You must be Laezel.|
|If there is a small part of you that wonders who you would be without the Queen and her foul codes, if you have ever dreamt of Prince Orpheus, we can bring him to life.|
|It imprisons the one who'll save us from Vlaakith.|

Synopsis: Avatar Laezel must pick between siding with Voss and helping Orpheus or siding with Vlaakith's Inquisitor in helping them kill Orpheus. They both lead to a fight with the opposing party.
